        "title": "feat: expose node-hosted plugin tools",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add `node.pluginTools.update` so connected node hosts can publish live agent-visible plugin/MCP tool availability after a successful Gateway connect and on reconnect.\n- Materialize trusted registry-backed node-host `agentTool` registrations as normal agent plugin tools, executing through `node.invoke` with node command allowlists, stale-connection checks, provider-safe names, and existing plugin tool policy.\n- Update node listing/catalog surfaces, MCP inventory classification, SDK/runtime docs, and gateway protocol docs for node-hosted plugin tools.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test packages/gateway-protocol/src/index.test.ts src/gateway/node-command-policy.test.ts src/gateway/node-registry.test.ts src/node-host/plugin-node-host.test.ts src/node-host/runner.test.ts src/agents/node-plugin-tools.test.ts src/agents/tool-search.test.ts src/agents/tools-effective-inventory.test.ts src/gateway/client.test.ts`\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test.tsbuildinfo`\n- `pnpm check:changed` via Testbox `tbx_01kt9wq1md053kaj7t33f9r9cf`, Actions run https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/26970011501\n- `autoreview --mode local` clean after accepted findings were fixed\n\n## Notes\n\nPond E2E was attempted for multi-node custom tool invocation. Direct Tailscale pond was blocked by invalid OAuth auth; local-container pond exposed the descriptor lifecycle bugs that this patch fixed. Clean multi-node live custom-tool invocation remains a proof gap beyond the automated Testbox and focused local coverage above.\n",
